          "The TYPE 2 HYPOTHETICAL — unreal",
          "present. Things that AREN'T true",
          "but COULD BE imagined.",
          "",
          "FORMULA:",
          "   se + imperfect subjunctive,",
          "        conditional",
          "",
          "EXAMPLES:",
          "   Se avessi più tempo, viaggerei.",
          "   = If I had more time, I'd travel.",
          "",
          "   Se fossi ricco, comprerei una",
          "   villa al mare.",
          "   = If I were rich, I'd buy a villa.",
          "",
          "   Se parlassi italiano, capiresti.",
          "   = If you spoke Italian, you'd get it."
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Se avessi tempo, viaggerei."
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "THE THREE HYPOTHETICAL TYPES:",
          "",
          "TYPE 1 — real/possible (Core):",
          "   se + present, future",
          "   Se piove, resto a casa.",
          "   (If it rains, I'll stay home.)",
          "",
          "TYPE 2 — unreal present (THIS):",
          "   se + imp. subj., conditional",
          "   Se piovesse, resterei a casa.",
          "   (If it rained, I'd stay home.)",
          "",
          "TYPE 3 — unreal past (Pareto 2):",
          "   se + pluperfect subj., cond. past",
          "   Se avesse piovuto, sarei restato.",
          "   (If it had rained, I'd have stayed.)",
          "",
          "Today you need Type 2. Type 3 later."
        ]
      }
    ]
